text: Damishah Charles (born 15 October 1997) is a Sint Maarten-born Dutch softball player. She started playing softball in Enschede from a young age.Profile at dutchsoftballteam.com In 2021 played with the softball club of Morgan State University in the United States where she studied. She is member of the Netherlands women's national softball team. With the national team she finished fourth at the World Championships. She became European champion at the 2022 Women's Softball European Championship. In 2021 Charles was officialy decorated by Edison Rijna of Bonaire. ==References== Category:1997 births Category:Living people Category:Dutch softball players Category:Sportswomen
